TITLE: Initializing tldraw with a Snapshot Prop
DESCRIPTION: Loads document and session state asynchronously, then provides it to the Tldraw component as a snapshot prop for initial state configuration.
SOURCE: https://github.com/tldraw/tldraw/blob/main/apps/docs/content/docs/persistence.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_4

LANGUAGE: tsx
CODE:
```
function MyApp({ userId, documentId }) {
	const [snapshot, setSnapshot] = useState(null)

	useEffect(() => {
		async function load() {
			const document = await getDocumentState(documentId)
			const session = await getSessionState(documentId, userId)
			setSnapshot({ document, session })
		}

		load()
	}, [documentId, userId])

	return snapshot ? <Tldraw snapshot={snapshot} /> : null
}
```

